    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make organ donation consent made prior to someone\u2019s death binding",
        "additional_details": "Under the current system, families are still consulted and can effectively prevent donation, even when a person has clearly stated their wishes. We think this undermines personal autonomy and can result in fewer lifesaving transplants.",
        "background": "We call on the Government to legislate so that a person\u2019s registered decision to donate is legally binding and cannot be overridden by family members after the person\u2019s death.",
